1
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:10,667
Raichu!

2
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:12,600
- Wait.
- Help!

3
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:13,900
Yen, hold on to me.

4
00:00:13,967 --> 00:00:15,000
What?

5
00:00:15,067 --> 00:00:16,033
I paid two months in advance
for our house.

6
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:18,033
They can't shoo us away
just like that.

7
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:19,367
The nerve of them!

8
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:21,100
Ouch! It hurts!

9
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:22,600
- I can't move it!
- Are you okay, Sab?

10
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:23,633
Why do you keep
coming back here?

11
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,167
- You stink!
- Fight me!

12
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,000
I won't fight you
because you stink!

13
00:00:27,067 --> 00:00:28,067
Take a bath first!

14
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:30,767
Why are you making it hard
for yourself?

15
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:34,267
It's so clear that Red
likes you.

16
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:39,567
I tried to be with Sabina,
but it's you that I like.

17
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:42,300
I miss our fun moments...

18
00:00:42,367 --> 00:00:44,400
our plans...

19
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:46,100
I really miss you.

20
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:47,900
We know everything about you!

21
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:50,567
And we're going to the village
chief to report you!

22
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,567
Are you not going to stop?

23
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:55,233
There will be no us as long as
there's Sabina.

24
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:58,367
Let's not make it difficult
for ourselves.

25
00:00:58,433 --> 00:00:59,567
We'll just go to the stream

26
00:00:59,633 --> 00:01:00,833
right in the middle
of the woods.

27
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:02,900
- I'll go with you.
- We can handle this.

28
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:05,267
You're safe here, there are no
wild animals around.

29
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:06,700
We're the only ones here.

30
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:07,967
Just get some rest.

31
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:09,000
I'll follow them.

32
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:10,800
We shouldn't have left Sabina
alone.

33
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:13,467
She's not feeling well.

34
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:14,867
I hate her!

35
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:16,433
I have to do something!

36
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:18,267
You have to do something?

37
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:19,800
Yen.

38
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:22,467
So your feet are okay now.

39
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:23,833
Oh, no, no.

40
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:26,767
Yenyen, let me explain.

41
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,500
No, you don't have to, Sabina.

42
00:01:28,567 --> 00:01:30,267
I already know the truth.

43
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:32,200
Why are you lying?

44
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:36,133
Why are you pretending
in front of Red?

45
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,233
Yenyen...

46
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:47,733
Actually, you're mistaken.

47
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,467
My feet still hurt.

48
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:50,900
I can stand just a little.

49
00:01:50,967 --> 00:01:53,333
But when I try to step it...

50
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:54,900
Ouch!

51
00:01:54,967 --> 00:01:57,067
- Can you help me, please?
- Drop the act, Sabina.

52
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:59,067
You make yourself look like
a fool.

53
00:02:00,067 --> 00:02:01,733
I heard everything.

54
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:06,933
I heard you're just pretending
to be hurt

55
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,167
to get Red's attention.

56
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:10,333
Yenyen, I...

57
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,167
That's enough, Sabina!

58
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,333
Just admit it!

59
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,133
Fine!

60
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,500
Okay, Yen.

61
00:02:20,567 --> 00:02:22,500
I'm just pretending.

62
00:02:22,567 --> 00:02:24,167
My feet never hurt.

63
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:25,600
It's just an act.

64
00:02:25,667 --> 00:02:27,300
You know why?

65
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:28,767
It's for Red!

66
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:30,600
So he'll be concerned about me.

67
00:02:30,667 --> 00:02:32,067
And you know why?

68
00:02:33,267 --> 00:02:34,833
It's because of you!

69
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:38,200
If you're not in the picture,
we could have stayed together!

70
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:41,300
He could have still loved me
like before!

71
00:02:41,367 --> 00:02:43,000
We could have been okay.

72
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:48,633
- Get lost!
- Leave this place!

73
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:51,000
Don't fight them.

74
00:02:51,067 --> 00:02:52,033
Just don't.

75
00:02:58,533 --> 00:02:59,967
You're right, Dindi.

76
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:03,700
I shouldn't stoop down
to their level.

77
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:05,833
These judgmental people!

78
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:09,167
Are you done yet?

79
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:11,633
Are you happy now after
what you did to me?

80
00:03:13,433 --> 00:03:18,100
Did hurting me make you
feel better?

81
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:23,367
Yes, I went to jail.

82
00:03:24,967 --> 00:03:27,600
But you don't know
what really happened.

83
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:29,433
Do you know me well?

84
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,433
You? Do you know me?

85
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:35,000
Do you know me to accuse me
like this?

86
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:44,233
What makes you different
from a criminal

87
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,000
by doing what you did?

88
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:53,567
I'm just new in your
neighborhood.

89
00:03:54,933 --> 00:04:00,500
I chose to start
a new life here.

90
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:06,500
Because I want to fix my life
and my daughter's life.

91
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:10,233
Don't I have that right?

92
00:04:12,767 --> 00:04:15,467
Don't I have the right
to change?

93
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:17,667
To start anew?

94
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,500
So was Red telling the truth?

95
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:24,867
You've broken up
before the accident.

96
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:29,367
Sabina, you lied to me!

97
00:04:30,933 --> 00:04:32,700
You lied to me!

98
00:04:33,367 --> 00:04:37,267
When you begged me, was that
a part of your acting show?

99
00:04:38,233 --> 00:04:41,667
I believe you because
you're a woman like me.

100
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:44,900
But you tricked me!

101
00:04:45,933 --> 00:04:49,167
You used my trust
to your advantage!

102
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:54,667
But no.

103
00:04:58,100 --> 00:04:59,867
Your pretension
should stop here.

104
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:00,867
I'm going to tell Red.

105
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,500
No, no, please!

106
00:05:02,567 --> 00:05:04,233
Yen, please!
Don't do that, please.

107
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,633
Don't tell Red, please.

108
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:07,933
I'm begging you, please.

109
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,567
I can't live without Red.

110
00:05:09,633 --> 00:05:11,100
Please, I'm begging you.

111
00:05:11,167 --> 00:05:12,933
I will do everything you want.

112
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,933
Just don't tell Red.

113
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,700
If you do that,
he will never forgive me.

114
00:05:17,767 --> 00:05:19,133
I'm begging you.

115
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,900
I can't live without Red.

116
00:05:20,967 --> 00:05:22,900
Please, Yenyen.
I'm begging you.

117
00:05:22,967 --> 00:05:23,933
Just help me.

118
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,267
Help us get back together.

119
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:28,000
Please, I will do anything.
Anything!

120
00:05:28,067 --> 00:05:29,900
Sabina, I don't believe you
anymore.

121
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:31,367
Anything, Yenyen, please!

122
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,633
Please!

123
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:34,600
Yenyen, come back here!

124
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,833
Come back here!

125
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:38,100
You can't be the reason
for our breakup!

126
00:05:38,167 --> 00:05:39,533
Come back here!

127
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,767
Let's just do this.

128
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:46,867
Confront me if you can prove
that I killed anyone here.

129
00:05:46,933 --> 00:05:48,833
Right here in your neighborhood!

130
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:54,367
But for now, let's stay out
of each other's business!

131
00:05:54,433 --> 00:05:56,333
I won't fight you.

132
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,667
As Lord once said...

133
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:59,633
when someone throws a stone
at you...

134
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:01,667
Don't you dare use God!

135
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:07,533
- Get lost!
- Amanda!

136
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,600
Shove a rice cake
down her throat!

137
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:19,067
Amanda, let's go! Stop it!

138
00:06:23,467 --> 00:06:25,500
Let's go Amanda.
Just leave them be!

139
00:06:59,933 --> 00:07:00,867
They're such a pest.
Now I have to pay for the
rice cake I shoved

140
00:07:01,567 --> 00:07:04,167
in that woman's mouth.

141
00:07:04,233 --> 00:07:08,967
I still can't believe how
you talked back to them.

142
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:10,567
They got what they deserved!

143
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,467
I hope they will stop now.

144
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:14,833
I will endure it
as long as I can.

145
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:18,833
But I know how to fight when
it's getting too much.

146
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,033
They're unbelievable.

147
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:22,400
But I have to go.

148
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:23,467
I'll be late for work.

149
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:24,800
It's too far from here.

150
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:25,867
I'll get going.

151
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:27,333
Okay.

152
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,133
Bye, Amanda. I'll be back.

153
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,267
Okay.

154
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:36,833
Hello?

155
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:37,900
Good day.

156
00:07:37,967 --> 00:07:40,267
Is this Mrs. Amanda Sta. Maria?

157
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:41,400
Speaking.

158
00:07:41,467 --> 00:07:44,100
This is Leah from the airlines.

159
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:47,367
We have an update regarding
the plane crash.

160
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,700
Are you sure?

161
00:07:54,767 --> 00:07:55,967
That's good news!

162
00:07:56,033 --> 00:07:57,033
Yes, yes.

163
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:58,333
I'll be on my way.
Thank you!

164
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,433
Thank you very much!
Thank you.

165
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:02,133
Who was that?

166
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,867
The airline called.

167
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:07,167
They said the search and
rescue team found things

168
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:08,500
on an island.

169
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:13,000
And they suspect that there are
survivors on the nearby islands.

170
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:14,800
Red might be there.

171
00:08:14,867 --> 00:08:16,767
He might still be alive.

172
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,200
I hope he's safe.

173
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:20,867
Hold on.

174
00:08:20,967 --> 00:08:22,700
We have a meeting
with Mr. Akashi.

175
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:24,567
We have a lot to talk about.

176
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:27,000
The Casino Amigo has a lot
of debts to pay.

177
00:08:27,067 --> 00:08:29,600
Look, Zandro.
That can all wait, okay?

178
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:31,900
I invested lots of money
in the business, okay?

179
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:35,467
And I can get them all back.

180
00:08:35,533 --> 00:08:37,500
But my son only lives once.

181
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:38,667
Try to understand.

182
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:40,600
My son has only one life
to live.

183
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:46,867
And I can't get my son's
life back.

184
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:55,133
Eden!

185
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:03,833
Red!

186
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:05,033
Raichu!

187
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:10,033
Red!

188
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:14,067
Where did they go?

189
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:23,967
Red!

190
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,700
Red! Raichu!

191
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,867
You can't tell Red!

192
00:09:37,233 --> 00:09:39,100
Why? What will you do, Sabina?

193
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:41,300
Are you going to hurt me?

194
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:43,367
I'm not scared of you.

195
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:44,433
Oh, really?

196
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,700
You're not scared?

197
00:09:45,767 --> 00:09:47,400
Then you leave me
with no choice.

198
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:48,933
Come here!
You're not going anywhere!

199
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,200
Stop it!

200
00:09:50,267 --> 00:09:51,767
Eden!

201
00:09:53,267 --> 00:09:54,333
Eden!

202
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,167
We're back!

203
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:06,067
I don't think they're here.

204
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:07,533
Where did they go?

205
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:09,900
I don't know.

206
00:10:09,967 --> 00:10:10,933
But for sure,
they didn't go far.

207
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,967
They must be somewhere near.

208
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:15,900
Let go of me, Sabina!

209
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,833
How dare you!

210
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:22,433
You're the most annoying thing
in our relationship!

211
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:25,433
You're the biggest liar and
schemer I have ever met!

212
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,533
You're shameless!

213
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,033
Stop it!

214
00:10:29,567 --> 00:10:31,467
Can you give me an update, Miss?

215
00:10:31,533 --> 00:10:33,767
My daughter's name
is Eden Sta. Maria.

216
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:34,967
Excuse me.

217
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,567
Just wait for now, we're just
waiting for something.

218
00:10:36,633 --> 00:10:38,133
Yes, I'm with Zandro.

219
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,200
We'll ask for updates.

220
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:42,033
Wait for me there.

221
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:44,167
I just finished my meeting
with the Singalong branch.

222
00:10:44,233 --> 00:10:45,933
I'm on my way there.

223
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,367
Yeah, I'll let you know.

224
00:10:47,433 --> 00:10:49,133
All right, thank you.

225
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,800
Excuse me, Miss.

226
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:53,033
I'm Rina Ramos.

227
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,867
I am the mother
of Roderick Ramos.

228
00:10:54,933 --> 00:10:56,767
Is there any news about him?

229
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:57,767
Actually...

230
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:58,867
Rina.

231
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:05,433
I will do everything in my power
to stop you

232
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,200
from ruining our relationship!

233
00:11:07,267 --> 00:11:08,300
How dare you!

234
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:11,233
You think you're that righteous?

235
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:15,200
I know you want us to break up
so you can have him!

236
00:11:15,267 --> 00:11:18,133
- Stop it!
- You're a wench!

237
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,567
Let me go!

238
00:11:19,633 --> 00:11:23,800
I won't ruin a relationship that
doesn't exist from the start!

239
00:11:23,867 --> 00:11:26,767
- Listen to me.
- Stop lying, Sabina!

240
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,900
How dare you! Come here!

241
00:11:28,967 --> 00:11:30,367
Let go of me!

242
00:11:30,433 --> 00:11:34,033
- Let me go!
- Stay away from my boyfriend!

243
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:35,833
Stay away from Red!

244
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,567
Stay away from Red!

245
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,867
Stay away from him!

246
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:43,567
Stop it!

247
00:11:46,433 --> 00:11:47,333
Yenyen!

248
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:51,067
Come back here!

249
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,567
So, where did they go?

250
00:12:03,633 --> 00:12:05,400
I don't know.

251
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:06,733
Sab can't walk.

252
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,500
Her feet are still hurting.

253
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:09,867
So, where did they go?

254
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,033
What are you doing here?

255
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:17,700
You might be forgetting.

256
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:21,067
My daughter was also
in the plane that crashed.

257
00:12:21,133 --> 00:12:23,433
I talked to her first.

258
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,033
And you came in
and squeezed by.

259
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,467
I don't give a damn about you.

260
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:34,233
You know, your opinion does not
matter to me.

261
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,067
Where's your manager?

262
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:38,900
I talked to him earlier.

263
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:40,267
Yes.

264
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:45,033
He told me to assist you
right away

265
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,767
and answer your questions.

266
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:49,067
Let's go to the VIP Lounge,
Ma'am.

267
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:51,233
Wait. Hold on.

268
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:53,400
I think you're being unfair.

269
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:58,900
I've been here for a while now,
while she just arrived.

270
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:00,733
We were talking, weren't we?

271
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:04,933
And you offered her a lounge?

272
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,300
VIP treatment?

273
00:13:06,367 --> 00:13:10,867
Sorry, Amanda,
if you don't have connections.

274
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:14,267
Just close your eyes
if you're envious.

275
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:16,333
That's not right.

276
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,433
Because you're not
the only one here

277
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,267
who has a family on that plane.

278
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,500
It's not just me.

279
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:24,133
Other people are here too.

280
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:28,767
I hope you can be fair.

281
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:31,100
We're all victims here.

282
00:13:31,167 --> 00:13:32,433
She's right, Miss!

283
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,467
You will give her
special treatment

284
00:13:34,533 --> 00:13:37,467
just because she knows
your manager?

285
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:38,867
Have some mercy.

286
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:40,767
Three of my family
were on that plane.

287
00:13:40,833 --> 00:13:42,933
Give us some consideration!

288
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,900
You can't have a VIP here!

289
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:46,600
We're going to file a complaint!

290
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:48,733
- Yen!
- Yenyen!

291
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:49,900
Yen!

292
00:13:52,533 --> 00:13:54,100
Yenyen!

293
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,300
Eden?

294
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,633
Where did they go?

295
00:14:05,433 --> 00:14:08,167
Let's split so we can find them
faster.

296
00:14:08,233 --> 00:14:09,533
Okay.

297
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,033
Eden!

298
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,067
Yen!

299
00:14:12,133 --> 00:14:13,200
Eden!

300
00:14:19,533 --> 00:14:20,667
Yenyen!

301
00:14:22,767 --> 00:14:23,800
Yen!

302
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:29,267
Yenyen!

303
00:14:29,367 --> 00:14:31,400
Come back here, Yenyen!

304
00:14:31,467 --> 00:14:34,233
I won't let you have
what you want!

305
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:46,033
Leave me alone, Sabina!

306
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,300
The more I won't leave you
alone!

307
00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:48,933
You and Red should not meet!

308
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,300
You can't ruin us!

309
00:15:09,967 --> 00:15:11,033
Yen!

310
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,967
- Yen, hold on to me!
- Red!

311
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:03,167
Will you just back off?

312
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:04,300
Back off, okay?

313
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:05,800
Don't get near her.
Back off.

314
00:16:05,867 --> 00:16:08,200
- Come on.
- You can't do that!

315
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,800
This is your fault, Amanda!

316
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:11,067
This is all your doing!

317
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:12,400
What? Me?

318
00:16:12,467 --> 00:16:14,633
Is it my fault?

319
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:18,233
I'm just talking on behalf
of everyone here.

320
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:20,833
Maybe you should blame karma.

321
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:23,300
That's karma.

322
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:29,533
What happened here?

323
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,900
Why are you fighting?

324
00:16:32,467 --> 00:16:33,667
And how did you end up here?

325
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:36,367
Aren't you injured, Sab?

326
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:39,167
- No, actually...
- Yeah, Sab.

327
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:41,633
Why don't you tell Red?

328
00:16:41,733 --> 00:16:43,367
Shut up, Yenyen.

329
00:16:43,433 --> 00:16:46,500
Why don't you tell him
the reason you're hurting me?

330
00:16:46,567 --> 00:16:48,900
Why don't you tell him why
you're stopping me

331
00:16:48,967 --> 00:16:50,200
from talking to him?

332
00:16:50,267 --> 00:16:51,300
Stopping?

333
00:16:51,367 --> 00:16:52,533
Why?

334
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:54,200
Because she's a liar, Red!

335
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:55,567
No, Yenyen!

336
00:16:57,133 --> 00:17:00,233
Actually, it still hurts...

337
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:01,967
I caught her.

338
00:17:02,033 --> 00:17:04,733
I saw her pretending
to have injured feet

339
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:06,733
to get your attention.

340
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,333
She lied to me.

341
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,667
Just shut up, Yenyen.

342
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:13,400
She lied that you two
are still okay.

343
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:15,767
So she can get you back.

344
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:18,200
Just admit it, Sabina!

345
00:17:18,267 --> 00:17:19,700
Tell the truth!

346
00:17:20,533 --> 00:17:22,667
Tell the truth,
especially to Red!

347
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:26,900
What is your issue?

348
00:17:26,967 --> 00:17:28,833
- Is my money an issue for you?
- Is this all about money?

349
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:30,833
Money? Okay, you want money?
Here.

350
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:31,867
Are you going to buy me
with your money?

351
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:35,700
You want my money?

352
00:17:35,767 --> 00:17:37,733
There you go!

353
00:17:52,867 --> 00:17:54,800
You're like dogs.

354
00:17:57,167 --> 00:18:00,933
You can do anything with money,
Amanda.

355
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:04,433
Too bad you don't have it.

356
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,667
How unlucky of you.

357
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:11,767
Excuse me, can I talk
to your manager now?

358
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,067
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Ramos,

359
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:16,233
but we can no longer grant
your request

360
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:17,933
for the spirit of fairness.

361
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,600
That's an order from
the upper management.

362
00:18:19,667 --> 00:18:22,233
We don't want any trouble.

363
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:23,767
What?

364
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:26,133
If you want to wait for updates
from the headquarters,

365
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,767
you have to wait
like the others.

366
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:29,133
I'm sorry.

367
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:33,067
This is all your doing.

368
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:35,767
It's your fault, Amanda.

369
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:37,067
My fault?

370
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:43,367
No, Red.

371
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:44,733
Don't believe that woman!

372
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:48,433
She's just making stuff up
to take you away from me.

373
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:50,267
She's lying.

374
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:51,900
Don't believe her.

375
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:53,633
My feet still hurt.

376
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:57,367
How dare you make those lies,
Sabina?

377
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,567
You're the one pretending.

378
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:04,400
You're the one who's good
at making up stories.

379
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:07,633
You're the one lying!

380
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:22,167
Excuse me, excuse me.

381
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:27,133
Rina, how is it going?

382
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,833
Is there an update?

383
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:29,933
Nothing.

384
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,500
And you know what's worse?

385
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:34,367
We can no longer use
the VIP Lounge.

386
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:37,067
Thanks to that envious woman!

387
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:39,133
You're upset.

388
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:41,833
It's not good for the two of you
to be in one place.

389
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:43,900
Come on.
Let's go to a coffee shop.

390
00:19:43,967 --> 00:19:44,967
What?

391
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,367
Come on.

392
00:20:02,433 --> 00:20:04,633
Can you stop, Yenyen?

393
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:06,600
It's true.

394
00:20:06,667 --> 00:20:09,167
You're the one who has motives.

395
00:20:09,233 --> 00:20:11,167
You wanted to get Red back.

396
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,067
You lied to us.

397
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:16,567
You made us look like a fool.

398
00:20:19,267 --> 00:20:21,833
Are you really that tough,
Sabina?

399
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:28,133
Will you carry on with your lies
for your sake?

400
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:37,767
You're just making
your sin worse.

401
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:40,533
Not to me.

402
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:43,100
To Red.

403
00:20:46,633 --> 00:20:49,000
Red, Red, no.

404
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:50,067
I'm really sorry.

405
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:51,100
Please just...

406
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:52,800
can you let me explain first?

407
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:54,300
Please?

408
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:57,467
So you really lied to me.

409
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,067
Liar!

410
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,967
I never thought you could
fool me like this!

411
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:08,667
You want to know why?

412
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:09,900
What?

413
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:11,733
Because of you!

414
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:14,500
You and Yenyen!

415
00:21:14,567 --> 00:21:17,600
I only wanted us to be okay.

416
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:21,300
And hear you say that
I'm the only one you love.

417
00:21:21,367 --> 00:21:23,700
But because that woman is here,

418
00:21:23,767 --> 00:21:26,133
I know that it's impossible
to happen.

419
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:29,333
Because you see nothing but her.

420
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,967
You only think of her.

421
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:38,033
I did it to save
our relationship!

422
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:44,733
So we could go back
to the way we were.

423
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:48,200
Everything that we had before,
everything.

424
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:52,200
That you love no one but me.

425
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:54,433
Is it hard to do, Red?

426
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,433
Sab! Sab, stop!

427
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:03,267
No matter how you push yourself
to me...

428
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:04,900
no matter how I tried...

429
00:22:04,967 --> 00:22:07,033
I can't love you.

430
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:10,633
Why don't we just accept it?

431
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,800
I meant every word.

432
00:22:16,233 --> 00:22:18,967
Let's just accept we're not
meant for each other.

433
00:22:20,533 --> 00:22:22,900
Someone else is meant for you.

434
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:24,400
Someone else will
appreciate you.

435
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:26,500
Someone will love you...

436
00:22:26,567 --> 00:22:29,100
more than I loved you.

437
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,300
Someone deserves your love.

438
00:22:33,367 --> 00:22:36,367
And that's not me, Sab.

439
00:22:36,433 --> 00:22:37,433
You don't mean that.

440
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:38,667
I'm sorry.

441
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:41,733
Red.

442
00:22:45,433 --> 00:22:46,433
Red!

443
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:52,233
Red, no. Please.

444
00:23:01,967 --> 00:23:03,933
Red!

445
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,467
You don't mean that.

446
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:07,467
You don't mean that.

447
00:23:12,633 --> 00:23:13,933
Oh my God!

448
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,267
Hello! We're here!

449
00:23:16,333 --> 00:23:18,033
- There are rescuers!
- Yenyen and Raichu should know.

450
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:19,200
We're here!

451
00:23:19,267 --> 00:23:20,867
Wait! Red, don't leave!

452
00:23:20,933 --> 00:23:22,667
They won't see us if you leave!

453
00:23:22,767 --> 00:23:24,200
- I need to tell them.
- Wait!

454
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:25,267
We're here!

455
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:26,967
There's news from
the headquarters

456
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:28,100
of the rescue team.

457
00:23:28,167 --> 00:23:29,467
There are two survivors.

458
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:32,467
One female and one male.

459
00:23:32,533 --> 00:23:35,900
Eden! Thank God you're here!

460
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:36,967
Raichu!

461
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,000
- This is Yenyen's.
- Red, we have to go back.

462
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:42,367
The rescuers might leave.

463
00:23:42,433 --> 00:23:45,000
I won't leave without Yenyen.

464
00:23:48,067 --> 00:23:49,033
Red!
